{{Eastern Slavic name|Khamzatovich|Aukhadov}}
'''Apti Khamzatovich Aukhadov''' ({{lang-ru|Апти Хамзатович Аухадов}}, born 18 November 1992) is a Russian [[weightlifter]] competing in the 85&nbsp;kg category. He is of [[Chechen people|Chechen]] descent. 

==Career==
Aukhadov was the world junior champion in 2010 and won silver at the [[2011 European Weightlifting Championships]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sport.francetv.fr/autres-sports/71598-halt%C3%A9rophilie-hennequin-en-bronze-%C3%A0-leuro|title=Haltérophilie - Hennequin en bronze à l'Euro|date=2011-04-15|publisher=[[France TV]]|language=fr|accessdate=11 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english2010/sports/2010-06/19/c_13357758.htm|title=Russian Aukhadov dominates men's 85kg at junior's weightlifting worlds|last=[[Xinhua News Agency]]|date=2010-06-19|publisher=English.news.cn |accessdate=11 August 2012}}</ref> He initially was awarded the silver medal at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] in the [[Weightlifting at the 2012 Summer Olympics – Men's 85 kg|men's 85 kg]] category with a total of 385&nbsp;kg.<ref>{{ Cite sports-reference | 1 =Apti Aukhadov| 2=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/au/apti-aukhadov-1.html | 3 = 11 August 2012}}</ref> Aukhadov took gold at the [[2013 World Weightlifting Championships]] with a combined total of 387&nbsp;kg.<ref>{http://www.wwc2013.pl/files/wyniki/wwc2013/85men.pdf}</ref>

In June 2016, it was announced by IWF that retests of the samples taken from the 2012 Olympics indicated that Aukhadov had tested positive for prohibited substances, namely [[Dehydrochloromethyltestosterone]] and [[Drostanolone]]. If confirmed, Aukhadov faced losing his Olympic medal and all results and medals earned from the date of the sample in 2012 to 2016.<ref>[http://www.iwf.net/2016/06/15/public-disclosures/ IWF public disclosures]</ref> In October 2016, he was stripped of his Olympic medal.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/weightlifting/37697300 "Apti Aukhadov stripped of London 2012 silver medal after sample tests positive"]. bbc.co.uk. 18 October 2016. Retrieved 18 October 2016.</ref><ref>[https://www.olympic.org/news/ioc-sanctions-two-athletes-for-failing-anti-doping-test-at-london-2012 IOC sanctions two athletes for failing anti-doping test at London 2012]</ref>

