ights, Part 1: Shaykh Ahmad ibn Zayn al-Din al-Ahsa'i|url=http://irfancolloquia.org/137/lambden_shining|journal=Lights of ‘Irfán: Papers Presented at the ‘Irfán Colloquia and Seminars|volume=17|pages=|via=}} * {{Cite book |last=Momen |first=Moojan |authorlink = Moojan Momen |title=An Introduction to Shi'i Islam: The History and Doctrines of Twelver Shi'ism |publisher=Yale University Press | year=1985 | isbn=0-300-03499-7 | pages = 229 | ref=harv}} *{{Cite journal |first=Moojan |last=Momen |authorlink=Moojan Momen |year=1991 |volume=Monograph #1 |pages=177 |title=The Works of Shaykh Ahmad al-Ahsá’í: A Bibliography |journal=Bahá’í Studies Bulletin |url=https://bahai-library.com/momen_shaykh_ahmad_bibliography |ref=harv }} * {{Cite book |last=A.L.M |first=Nicolas |title=Essai sur le cheikhisme |publisher=Paul Geuthner |location=Paris, France |year=1910 |ref=harv }} * Rafati, Vahid (1979). ''[http://bahaistudies.net/td/DevelopmentofShaykhiThought-pp1-48(Rafati).pdf The Development of Shaykhi Thought in Shi`i Islam]''. Ph.D. dissertation, University of California, Los Angeles. * {{cite book |first=Nabil |last=Zarandi |authorlink=Nabíl-i-A`zam |year=1932 |orig-year=Written in 1887-88 |title=Nabíl’s Narrative of the Early Days of the Bahá’í Revelation |title-link=The Dawn-Breakers |edition=Hardcover |translator-first=Shoghi |translator-last=Effendi |translator-link=Shoghi Effendi |publisher=Bahá'í Publishing Trust |location=Wilmette, Illinois, USA |isbn=0-900125-22-5 |ref=harv }}
